document.pageTitle: The Résonances de Cartier Launch Gala Was One Chic Affair
document.pageMetaDescription: Check out all the must-see looks from the red carpet of the Résonances de Cartier launch gala on Governors Island in New York.

document.contentBody:
[
  {
    "type": "paragraph",
    "label": "Paragraph",
    "content": "On Wednesday night, **[Cartier](http://www.harpersbazaar.com.au/fashion/sofia-coppola-and-cartier-partnership-3537|target="_blank")** threw a chic little (read: huge) soirée in celebration of the launch of its Résonances de Cartier jewellery collection.

A party was held on Governor’s Island in [New York City](http://www.harpersbazaar.com.au/fashion/street-style-new-york-fashion-week-2-ss18-14301|target="_blank")—here that means the *entire* island, which was “privatised” for the night—and included Cartier-branded trolley-trains to ferry guests around, a fleet of taxi boats and black cars, and a custom-constructed 20,000-square-foot pavilion, according to *[Observer](http://observer.com/2017/10/cartier-high-jewelry-launch-governors-island/|target="_blank"|rel="nofollow").*

In attendance were actresses **Diane Kruger**, **Carey Mulligan**, and **Sofia Boutella**, whilst models **Jessica Hart**, **Carolyn Murphy** and **Alexandra Richards** also got glammed up for the night.

During the gala, guests were treated to performances by Audra Day, Jon Batiste and Grandmaster Flash, and were given personalised tins of caviar as gifts (now that’s how you do party favours). 

Take a scroll through our favourite looks from the night."
  }
]
